escribing the failure of successive governments to address problems faced by the public broadcaster, this book explains how the CBC lost its place in sports, drama, and entertainment. Taras and Waddell propose a way forward for the CBC – one in which the corporation concentrates its resources on news and current affairs and re-establishes a reputation for depth and quality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPublic broadcastingzCanada. 0aSocial mediazCanada. 4aCoursebook. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aBroadcasting Act.  aCBC, attention economy.  aCRTC.  aCanada-news and information.  aCanadian culture.  aCanadian media.  aCanadian programming.  aPublic broadcasting.  abroadcasting policy.  adigital transformation.1 aWaddell, Christopher, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148759355140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487593551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487593551.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles